The paper deals with the detection of botnets in network traffic, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed framework uses Neural Networks with Bayesian Regularization, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.NE) and statistical methods (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of feature selection and extraction techniques, which are commonly used in the field of signal processing and information retrieval (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for classification, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
